## 3. Backend Modules — File-by-File

### [server.mjs](file:///D:/Major/backend/server.mjs) — Application Entry Point
- Initialises Express app on `PORT` (default 5000)
- Sets up CORS (reads `FRONTEND_ORIGINS` from [.env](file:///D:/Major/backend/.env), supports multiple comma-separated origins)
- Mounts all route modules under `/api/*`
- Connects to MongoDB via [connectDB()](file:///D:/Major/backend/config/db.mjs#11-37)
- Calls [initScheduler()](file:///D:/Major/backend/utils/scheduler.mjs#16-32) on startup
- Runs a **background Offer follow-up processor** every 5 minutes (sends reminder emails to pending donors)
- Global error handler (catches 413 payload-too-large and other errors)

---

### [config/db.mjs](file:///D:/Major/backend/config/db.mjs) — Database Connection
- Connects to MongoDB using `mongoose.connect(MONGO_URI)`
- `serverSelectionTimeoutMS: 5000` to fail fast
- Fallback logic: if `mongodb+srv://` SRV DNS lookup fails, retries with `MONGO_URI_FALLBACK`

---

